"n.宁静，安静 【考】 abandon : inhibition / tranquillity : agitation(放纵无抑制/宁静无 骚动)反义词：commotion( 骚动); ferment(骚动); turbulence(骚动); pandemonium(大混乱) n. 宁静, 安静 【记】tranquil(adj 安静的), tran = trans转变, quil = quiet(adj 静止的; 宁静的); 参: tranquilizer(n 镇定剂) 【类】abandon: inhibition = tranquility: agitation放纵不会抑制 = 宁静不会骚动 【反】commotion(n 骚动); ferment(n 发酵; 动乱); turbulence(n 骚乱); pandemonium(n 混战场; 大混乱) 【记】trans 穿越 + equal 或quiet 平静 tranquility (n.)  also tranquillity, late 14c., from Old French tranquilite ""peace, happiness"" (12c.), from Latin tranquillitatem (nominative tranquillitas) ""quietness, stillness; serenity,"" from tranquillus ""quiet, calm, still,"" perhaps from trans- ""over"" (here in its intensive sense of ""exceedingly"") + a root possibly related to quies ""rest"" (see quiet (n.))."
